* About

 Greg is a framework for testing other programs and libraries.
 Its purpose is to provide a single front end for all tests and to
 be a small, simple framework for writing tests.
 Greg leverages off the Guile language to provide all the power (and more)
 of other test frameworks with greater simplicity and ease of use.

 Please send bug reports to https://gna.org/bugs/?group=greg or
 greg-devel@gna.org

* greg dependencies

 greg depends from this packages, need them to build and run:
	
	Guile: http://www.gnu.org/software/guile/  
		The guile scheme implementation
	libc, gcc and so on...
 
* greg Documentation

 The doc directory contains the reference manual  and some examples.

 The www pages are at http://www.gnu.org/software/greg or
 http://home.gna.org/greg/

 The project page is at: http://www.gna.org/projects/greg.

* Development versions

 greg source code is mantained using gnu arch. Main archives mirror
 can be found at:

 archive: baux@member.fsf.org--2005-greg
 location: http://arch.gna.org/upload/greg/2005-greg

 branches: 
    greg--baux   (my personal brench)
    greg--devel  (development, tag to this if you'd like to 
      contribute)
    greg--stable (released versions).
    greg-wpages  (web pages).

 Have a look at gnu arch manuals.    

